<normalizedToken id="8BD581209C097FDF51ADB4B7FC210A56" originalValue="Céterach" pageId="null" pageNumber="137">Ceterach</normalizedToken>
</pageBreakToken>
Willd.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="13D416C6A02FAC1786FF875B93BC40E0" pageId="null" pageNumber="137" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="822CACF1FE22B276619B960C3A8AD407" pageId="null" pageNumber="137">Schriftfarn</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="9E81B2783DC1766900E459B1283D2590" pageId="null" pageNumber="137" type="description">
<paragraph id="1184118572C00A6058F9DD1481E2F6C6" pageId="null" pageNumber="137">
Kleine Farne. Rhizom kurz, senkrecht. 
<normalizedToken id="F9C29AD55D3C2903B4CA56FFA3CDD6B8" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="137">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
fleischig oder lederig, 
<normalizedToken id="05E91020CCE9D48DCF12BCF115DE7C9F" originalValue="mehrjährig" pageId="null" pageNumber="137">mehrjaehrig</normalizedToken>
, 1fach fiederteilig oder 1-2fach gefiedert; 
<emphasis id="C12D0E14BCA058800F7DF2E701749BCE" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="137">Unterseite dicht mit dachziegelartig angeordneten Spreuschuppen</emphasis>
oder 
<normalizedToken id="E9AF0088D9437E1018808B09D1AD56B9" originalValue="Drüsenhaaren" pageId="null" pageNumber="137">Druesenhaaren</normalizedToken>
bedeckt. 
<emphasis id="FC183DC0CC2AA01819B7DE335FC2D6E4" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="137">
Sori 
<normalizedToken id="9AD55FE8AE9A6F6949BFA49DAEA8B7CD" originalValue="strichförmig" pageId="null" pageNumber="137">strichfoermig</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
, mit sehr schmalem Schleier oder ohne Schleier.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1A91F62D8102A4C481F01C29C243E322" pageId="null" pageNumber="137">
Die Gattung 
<emphasis id="48E4B10B5DEF91D6356938118FCF34DB" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="137">
<normalizedToken id="75593FC465FB7EF9E44D4BFE5E4EBDFC" originalValue="zählt" pageId="null" pageNumber="137">zaehlt</normalizedToken>
etwa 6 Arten; alle besiedeln trockene Standorte; 5 Arten in den Tropen;
</emphasis>
in 
<taxonomicName id="E03B2F060F2507A7BB2A22CD2F21C527" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Europa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="null" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Europa</taxonomicName>
nur 
<emphasis id="F5CB3B41975E33D445D9776FF020B435" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="137">
<taxonomicName id="27D3B33BD735E095FC6B54CB49C5FA7E" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Cystopteridaceae" genus="Cystopteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="null" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="officinarum">C. officinarum</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
